        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 8:43PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 843 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Walnut Grove to McKibben, and moving southeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Covington, Social Circle, Oxford, Porterdale, Walnut Grove, Newborn,
Mansfield, Jersey, Stewart, Turtle Cove, Worthville, Starrsville,
Brick Store, Herndonville, Eudora, North Alcovy, Fincherville, Stark,
and Rocky Plains.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
